snippet: In an interview with The Times, Ms. Hill said she was bothered by what she saw as the presumption that a woman would become vice president.
lead_paragraph: Anita Hill, whose treatment during Justice Clarence Thomas’s confirmation hearing has become an issue in the 2020 campaign, said she worries that the Democratic women in the race “are not being taken seriously as presidential candidates.”
abstract: In an interview with The Times, Ms. Hill said she was bothered by what she saw as the presumption that a woman would become vice president.

headline_main: Should Democrats Rally Around Joe Biden to Beat Trump?

snippet: Not the fight over abortion. Not the fight over impeachment. Maybe Biden? Nah.
lead_paragraph: Bret Stephens: Hi there, Gail. Until last week or so, I think there was a fairly broad consensus (including between the two of us) that impeachment was not a great idea. But now a Republican congressman, Michigan’s Justin Amash, has declared that Donald Trump has “engaged in impeachable conduct,” and the debate has resumed in earnest. Are you rethinking your earlier misgivings about impeachment?
abstract: Not the fight over abortion. Not the fight over impeachment. Maybe Biden? Nah.

snippet: Joe Biden makes his supporters feel safe, but nominating him is risky.
lead_paragraph: On Saturday afternoon, at Joe Biden’s official campaign kickoff rally in Philadelphia, I asked every attendee I met why they were supporting, or at least considering supporting, the former vice president. Often, they mentioned other people whom they thought Biden might appeal to. Again and again, they said they cared about beating Donald Trump above all else.
abstract: Joe Biden makes his supporters feel safe, but nominating him is risky.

snippet: The president held a rally on Monday in an area replete with culturally conservative, white, working-class voters whose energy in 2016 delivered the state’s 20 electoral votes to Mr. Trump.
lead_paragraph: MONTOURSVILLE, Pa. — President Trump’s presence in a district in north central Pennsylvania was not really needed to help the Republican congressional candidate who is heavily favored in a special election on Tuesday.
abstract: The president held a rally on Monday in an area replete with culturally conservative, white, working-class voters whose energy in 2016 delivered the state’s 20 electoral votes to Mr. Trump.

headline_main: Trump Holds Rally in Pennsylvania to Help a Congressional Candidate, and Himself
headline_print_headline: Trump Campaigns in Pennsylvania for a House Candidate, and for Himself

snippet: The recovery, which has brought low unemployment and rising wages elsewhere, hasn’t really lifted industrial northeast Ohio. But President Trump has lost little of his support there.
lead_paragraph: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio — In May 2016, David Betras, a Democratic Party leader in the heart of industrial northeast Ohio, sent a memo warning Hillary Clinton’s campaign that it was on the verge of losing Ohio, Pennsylvania and Michigan because she was not connecting with blue-collar voters. These states “should be easy wins for us,’’ he wrote.
abstract: The recovery, which has brought low unemployment and rising wages elsewhere, hasn’t really lifted industrial northeast Ohio. But President Trump has lost little of his support there.

snippet: In an interview, the longtime Democratic leader of the Senate discussed President Trump, his party’s primary and its lack of congressional candidates.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Former Senator Harry Reid of Nevada has called President Trump the “worst president” in American history. Mr. Trump has said the former Senate Democratic leader’s “failed career” was marked by “lies and deception.”
abstract: In an interview, the longtime Democratic leader of the Senate discussed President Trump, his party’s primary and its lack of congressional candidates.
